		<h3>
		<a class="icon-right-arrow" onclick="exp(event,'div','exp3')">SAP BusinessObjects Business Intelligence platform support</a>
		</h3>
			<div exp3='yes' style="display:none;padding:0 15px;">
			<p>Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects is a Java web application; it supports Java application servers that require standard J2EE deployment archives such as .war files. Although Esri has performed rigorous testing only on SAP BusinessObjects BI platforms deployed on Apache Tomcat web application servers, it is expected that the application will operate in any certified configuration of SAP BusinessObjects Business Intelligence platform 4.0 SP08 or later installed on a Java web application server running Java Servlet 2.5 or later.</p>
			<p>Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects server-side components must be installed on a 64-bit system.</p>
			<p>Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects is certified for the following versions of SAP BusinessObjects Business Intelligence platform:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>4.0 SP08 / SP09 / SP10</li>
					<li>4.1 SP03 / SP04 / SP05</li>
				</ul>
			<p>Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects server-side components have been tested on the following operating systems. To add the operating system of your SAP BusinessObjects Business Intelligence platform deployment this list, contact <a href="http://support.esri.com/phonesupport#us" target=blank>Esri Technical Support</a>.</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Windows Server 2008 R2</li>
					<li>Windows Server 2008 SP2</li>
					<li>Windows Server 2012</li>
					<li>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.5</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			
