			<div exp7='yes' style="display:none;padding:0 15px;">
			<p>Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects requires an already configured and functional SAP BusinessObjects Business Intelligence platform environment with its required web server environment (such as built-in Tomcat or optional third-party supported web server environment), other supporting applications or database servers, and a configured and functional SAP BusinessObjects Dashboards environment. SAP Technical Support aids in the deployment of SAP BusinessObjects with these components. Esri Technical Support aids in the deployment (and use) of the Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects add-on within an operational configuration of SAP BusinessObjects.</p>
			
			<p>Esri Technical Support analysts are not experts in all possible configurations of SAP BusinessObjects. Similarly, SAP Technical Support engineers are not experts in all aspects of an operational configuration of Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects. If you are experiencing a problem configuring SAP BusinessObjects, it is often more efficient to obtain help from SAP Technical Support. Similarly, if you are experiencing a configuration problem with third-party components within the larger SAP BusinessObjects environment, such as the dedicated web server environment, it is more efficient to get help from the third party's support organization. In cases where a problem is deemed to be in Esri Maps for SAP BusinessObjects, Esri Technical Support can be available to work with SAP Technical Support, third-party vendors, or their consultants.</p>
			
